what you're talking about.

01:24.500 --> 01:26.000
( clears throat )

01:29.083 --> 01:30.458
God, I miss Naomi.

01:37.291 --> 01:39.041
What are you--?
What are you doing?

01:39.083 --> 01:40.625
Just calm down.

01:40.667 --> 01:42.875
Massaging the area
helps to absorb the hormones.

01:42.917 --> 01:46.083
I'm deriving absolutely
no pleasure from this

01:46.125 --> 01:47.709
whatsoever.

01:47.750 --> 01:50.000
ADDISON:
Well, ahem, thank you.

01:53.083 --> 01:55.041
Now it's congratulations.

01:55.083 --> 01:57.041
Well, my FSH is really high.

01:57.083 --> 02:00.166
I don't know if I'll get any
good eggs out of it.

02:00.208 --> 02:02.083
It's still congratulations.
There's no way to know

02:02.125 --> 02:04.792
unless you try
and you're trying.

02:10.000 --> 02:11.917
WES:
It's not safe.
No one should go up.

02:11.959 --> 02:13.041
Wes. Wes.

02:13.083 --> 02:14.875
No one is gonna do anything
to you, honey.

02:14.917 --> 02:16.542
You wanted to give them
your painting.

02:16.583 --> 02:17.667
I'm not going up there.

02:17.709 --> 02:19.333
I don't wanna be here, Mom.
It's not safe.

02:19.375 --> 02:21.792
No one should get in there.
Karen. Wes. Everything okay?

02:21.834 --> 02:23.333
He's refusing to take
his heart meds.

02:23.375 --> 02:25.000
He's refusing
to take any meds.

02:25.041 --> 02:27.792
Hey, Wes. Is this your painting
here? It's really beautiful.

02:27.834 --> 02:30.458
Is that this building, Wes?
Yeah. The elevators hear.

02:30.500 --> 02:31.583
They hear you.
SAM: Right.

02:31.625 --> 02:32.709
They want you to go in.

02:32.750 --> 02:34.041
Know who would love
to see this?

02:34.083 --> 02:36.166
I'm not going up.
Dr. Turner.

02:36.208 --> 02:37.375
Dr. Turner, Wes.

02:37.417 --> 02:39.083
Why don't we both take
the stairs up--?

02:39.125 --> 02:41.542
They hear you
and they watch you.

02:41.583 --> 02:44.041
He needs to start seeing
her again. He's in trouble.

02:44.083 --> 02:46.000
Everything's gonna be okay.
Why don't you--?

02:46.041 --> 02:47.125
I can't go up there.
All right.

02:47.166 --> 02:48.125
I can't be here.

02:48.166 --> 02:49.500
I can't. I can't. I can't.

02:49.542 --> 02:51.333
KAREN:
Take that.

02:55.750 --> 02:57.041
( door opens )

03:00.750 --> 03:02.083
Ah!

03:02.125 --> 03:04.542
I can't believe you have been
running around Italy

03:04.583 --> 03:07.041
for six months.
I'm jealous.

03:07.083 --> 03:08.583
Don't be jealous.
Just go.

03:08.625 --> 03:11.750
And get the pizza in Naples.
It is insane.

03:11.792 --> 03:13.542
And then head straight
to Rome,

03:13.583 --> 03:16.166
buy a large box of condoms
and never leave.

03:16.208 --> 03:19.583
Italian men are ridiculous.
And they're everywhere.

03:19.625 --> 03:20.959
Italian men in Italy?

03:21.000 --> 03:23.583
Just standing around
in Armani suits, eating gelato.

03:23.625 --> 03:26.041
Waiting to get attacked
by a predatory American tourist.

03:26.083 --> 03:30.417
Never a tourist.
There I am che donna stupenda.

03:30.458 --> 03:31.417
A hot piece of ass.

03:31.458 --> 03:33.208
Ha-ha-ha.
Ha-ha-ha.

03:37.083 --> 03:38.375
When did your symptoms
start?

03:38.417 --> 03:40.583
Couple months ago,
in Ravello.

03:40.625 --> 03:41.875
We can try meds.

03:41.917 --> 03:43.667
There are ways that
we can manage your symptoms.

03:43.709 --> 03:45.166
Amelia, thanks to you,

03:45.208 --> 03:47.166
I had a beautiful six months
in Italy,

03:47.208 --> 03:50.208
which I wouldn't have had,
and I am grateful.

03:50.250 --> 03:52.792
So grateful.

03:52.834 --> 03:56.500
But I'm not gonna die
a slow death from Huntington's.

03:56.542 --> 03:59.041
I am not going the way
my mother did.

03:59.083 --> 04:01.041
I'm not. You promised.
Michelle-- I know, but--

04:01.083 --> 04:02.709
It's time, Amelia.

04:02.750 --> 04:06.417
I mean, I've had great food,

04:06.458 --> 04:08.500
great sex,

04:08.542 --> 04:10.041
great love in my life.

04:10.083 --> 04:11.291
And a great friend.

04:11.333 --> 04:14.041
I'm happy.

04:14.083 --> 04:15.291
And I'm ready.

04:16.333 --> 04:19.917
I need you
to help me die.

04:29.500 --> 04:30.542
( knocking on door )

04:30.583 --> 04:32.500
VIOLET:
All right, you wanna open it?

04:32.542 --> 04:35.250
All right. Open it up.

04:35.291 --> 04:37.041
Hi. Hey, Uncle Sam.
How you doing?

04:37.083 --> 04:38.417
Hey, buddy.

04:38.458 --> 04:40.834
Hey, have you ever, um,
baked anything?

04:40.875 --> 04:42.542
Like tried to bake?
Because it's hard.

04:42.583 --> 04:44.500
Really hard.

04:44.542 --> 04:45.750
I had no idea how hard it was.

04:45.792 --> 04:47.917
It's harder than med school.
Yeah.

04:47.959 --> 04:50.000
We have a little 2-year-old
sous-chef here.

04:50.041 --> 04:51.959
( Violet mimics airplane
propeller whirring )

04:52.000 --> 04:53.458
LUCAS: I want candy.
SAM: I...

04:53.500 --> 04:55.250
Yes. You.
Why are you here?

04:55.291 --> 04:57.083
It's Wes.
Do you remember him?

04:57.125 --> 04:58.583
Patient, the painter.
I know Wes.

04:58.625 --> 05:00.709
He's off his meds.

05:00.750 --> 05:02.542
Psych meds or heart meds?
All of them.

05:02.583 --> 05:04.166
He won't see Sheldon,
he won't listen to me.

05:04.208 --> 05:05.875
You're the only one he trusts.

05:05.917 --> 05:08.041
I know that you can't talk
to him officially,

05:08.083 --> 05:09.291
but--
Damn it.

05:09.333 --> 05:11.709
Unofficially,
I was thinking maybe--

05:11.750 --> 05:13.583
Yeah. I'll get a sitter.
All right.

05:13.625 --> 05:15.041
Watch him for a minute?
Yeah.

05:15.083 --> 05:16.834
What's happening,
buddy boy?

05:19.083 --> 05:21.041
If you and Mason are gonna be
seeing each other,

05:21.083 --> 05:23.500
we should set some rules.

05:23.542 --> 05:25.458
Ground rules. Okay.
Yeah.

05:30.834 --> 05:33.291
First, your wife--
Yeah.

05:33.333 --> 05:37.041
--is not allowed to speak to
Mason or be anywhere near him.

05:37.083 --> 05:39.000
Charlotte should never
have done what she did,

05:39.041 --> 05:41.125
but she's sorry.

05:41.166 --> 05:43.625
She's actually very different
once you get to know her.

05:43.667 --> 05:45.625
No, thanks.
Secondly,

05:45.667 --> 05:48.250
I don't want you telling Mason
that you're his father.

05:49.542 --> 05:51.709
Ever?
For now.

05:51.750 --> 05:54.625
Okay. If you wanna see Mason,
those are my conditions.

05:59.709 --> 06:03.083
Beautiful. All of this is
so beautiful.

06:06.375 --> 06:08.834
The colors.
The textures.

06:08.875 --> 06:12.709
Everything around us.
It's life on a canvas.

06:16.500 --> 06:20.041
Hey, Wes. It's me.

06:20.083 --> 06:23.834
It's Dr. Turner.
Do you remember me?

06:23.875 --> 06:25.041
( scoffs )

06:25.083 --> 06:29.291
You're not Dr. Turner.
Yes. Yes, I am.

06:33.125 --> 06:34.709
Listen to me, Wes.

06:34.750 --> 06:36.792
Do you remember when we
started working together

06:36.834 --> 06:38.875
and you were living in a box
on Venice Beach?

06:38.917 --> 06:40.041
Do you remember that?

06:40.083 --> 06:41.500
And I used to come
visit you

06:41.542 --> 06:44.291
and we would talk about
how you were feeling.

06:44.333 --> 06:48.250
About the voices in your head,
the ones that frightened you.

06:48.291 --> 06:49.625
You're not Dr. Turner.

06:49.667 --> 06:52.291
Remember what happened
after that?

06:52.333 --> 06:54.375
